details.place_name: The Chai Window at Twenty Two West
details.description: Embedded in the Twenty Two West studio and storefront is our cozy Chai Window, where we serve up cups of beautifully spiced, rich organic tea made in house from whole spices, velvety oat milk, and softly sweetened with coconut sugar. Each sip adds a layer of warmth, creating a true sip and shop experience!

raw_data.name_for_emails: The Chai Window At Twenty Two West

raw_data.owner_title: The Chai Window at Twenty Two West

reviews_data.review_text:
Great place to enjoy some chai drinks and treats and do a little shopping too.

The iced chai was so pretty and tasty too. The flavor was a little subtle for my tastes but it was still very refreshing. I saw some other customers order the chai popsicles and they looked so fun!

The little parking lot behind the house is clutch on that busy street where parking is hard to come by.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Raquel! We definitely look forward to seeing you again!

reviews_data.review_text:
This was quite a unique experience. First, you need eagle eyes to find it. The address is only posted on the mailbox. They also have two signs in the yard. Otherwise, you'll need to circle around the block to find it. As this was once a house, the driveway served as the entrance and exit to the backyard, which was covered into their parking lot.

The Chai Window is literally a window on the side of the house. There are two small tables inside for you to sit and drink your chai. Yet, the main attraction is the jewelry and home decor room.

With that side, I felt the drinks were an afterthought. While they offered hot or iced chai, they did not offer any add-ons such as syrups or different flavors. They did have a chai ice cream sandwich and popsicle on the menu. However, they were sold out when I went. Overall, I might try a drink or sweet treat if I were attending one of their event. Otherwise, I would recommend a traditional tea or sweet shop.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for coming to visit us! I'm glad you felt the care and intention we put into the shop and loved getting to see where each piece was made in house. We also absolutely love having the chai window as a way to welcome people into our shop with a thoughtfully made cup of chai. I completely understand your desire for syrups, we just don't offer them because everything we do is refined sugar free and we are steeping the organic Assam tea with fresh ginger and hand muddled spices to create a beautifully balanced cup of chai. We hope to see you again soon and really appreciate your support!

reviews_data.review_text:
Got a hot chai. Taste great! Especially loved that it did not add any sugar.
There is a small rest area inside as well as seating at the front yard.
Parking is limited, but good enough for grab and go.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for coming to see us Siran! I'm so glad you loved the chai and found it to be nicely balanced. We look forward to seeing you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
I have been driving past this spot for months now and so glad I was able to enjoy it today. The chai is delicious and cooling for these hot summer days. The area is well decorated and I love all the plants and the colors. I will definitely have to come back for more.

They have very beautiful jewelry made in house and I’d love to get some of their pieces one day. Great gift idea.

The staff were very friendly and helpful. She explained how they make the jewelry at the store. All in all a great experience.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Awe I'm so glad today was the day! Thanks so much for stopping by and happy our studio, storefront, and chai window were a bright spot in your day. Thanks for keeping us in mind for your gifts and we look forward to seeing you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
Tucked inside a charming boutique, The Chai Window might look small from the outside, but don’t let that fool you—this little spot has big personality!

The boutique is a delightful mix of handmade charm and local finds. Half is a crafty haven, with jewelry being made right on site (with custom options too!), and the other half tempts you with dreamy candles, incense, and scattered treasures that make you want to explore every shelf.

Just between the shop and The Chai Window is the cutest little nook perfect for reading, journaling, or simply sipping and relaxing. It’s cozy, calm, and full of warm, welcoming vibes.

I ordered an iced chai and liked the sweet detail of a real flower taped to the cup. Such a small thing, but it made me smile big. The chai itself was perfectly refreshing and full of flavor for a hot summer day.

Whether popping in for a quick sip or staying a while to soak in the cozy vibes, The Chai Window is a spot worth checking out.
reviews_data.owner_answer: How incredibly kind! I'm beyond happy that you enjoyed your time at my studio, storefront, and chai window. The flowers really do add that perfect little bit of extra joy don't they :) You're welcome truly anytime and we look forward to seeing you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I drove by this place for so long having no idea it was there but I’m so glad I saw a TikTok one day that pointed it out! As a chai lover this was delicious. I love a spicy chai and the ginger and cinnamon were perfectly balanced. Dairy free too! The owner was very kind and I always love a woman owned/ran business!! Also bonus points for the cute little wildflower they put on every cup! The jewelry store attached was very cute and all hand made which is awesome. I definitely want to make my way back here to fill up my punch card! 😆
reviews_data.owner_answer: Woohoo!! I'm so glad you stopped by and appreciate your support so much. Haha I love it - we will see you for more punches in that card soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I love coming here! The chai is so tasty, and I really appreciate that it comes made with oat milk. Each person who works the window is so kind and pleasant. Often they go above and beyond like taping little flowers to the cups. I also realllllly love the shape of the cups. It may be silly, but it really elevates the experience. I’ve come here enough to fill up almost two punch cards, and I’ll keep coming back!
reviews_data.owner_answer: The sweetest words ever - my day is made! I'm so glad you've been loving your trips to The Chai Window and we will see you again soon for your next card punch!

reviews_data.review_text: Ive been wanting to try this place for a long time now. It’s super cute and homey. They do have a few seats inside to hang out at. Service is nice and friendly. I love chai, but I wasn’t too big of a fan of their chai. I feel like it was watered down and had less flavor. Maybe because I did get it iced, and I normally get it hot.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for coming to try our chai Nia!

reviews_data.review_text:
I pass by this establishment all the time while working, so I ventured there with my wife on a Saturday afternoon and was pleased with the shop.

It has a nice charm to it; it has a cozy and familiar atmosphere akin to the Charlotte of yesteryear.

The staff is very welcoming and personable, there’s nestled seating inside and a bench outside to enjoy a very pleasant space out back.

And yes, I did enjoy my cold Chai drink! It satisfied without relying on any one ingredient; making a refreshing sip and chat with my beautiful spouse!

It’s the kind of business I look forward to returning to. They even have goods that they sell also, making the trip a delight.

Give it your time, so you can have a moment to see what makes NoDa, well, NoDa.
reviews_data.owner_answer: This is the best - we love our city and being part of the league of small local businesses that makes our neighborhood so special. We look forward to seeing you and your wife again soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
The Chai Window was amazing! The Cold Chai was perfectly balanced & not too sweet—you could tell that the Chai was of quality.

The aesthetically pleasing colors and natural scents within Twenty Two West overall read charming, artsy and calming—as a Charlotte native, It felt like a nod to old NoDa.

I love that they have workshops and that their jewelry is handmade, I will definitely be back.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your support Laurisha! We will see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Have been meaning to try the Chai Window for a while having had it recommended to me by several of my clients. Just stopped by on my way home and had a delightful experience. Felt so welcomed by the friendly staff and by the time I had paid and turned around to literally smell the flowers (jasmine growing on the handrail) my iced chai was ready. My drink was lightly spicy and not too sweet — just the way a chai should be (and the flower on the cup was a sweet touch!) A great addition to all the wonderful local businesses opening or moving to this stretch of The Plaza.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind review Alex! I'm so glad you came to see us and loved your chai. We've been so loving the jasmine growing this spring too :)

reviews_data.review_text: Adorable, picture-worthy, friendly and delicious!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much Ryan! I'm so glad you enjoyed your visit to The Chai Window and we hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I stopped by The Chai Window at 22 West, and it was an absolute delight! The chai was quick, simple, and incredibly refreshing, with a depth of flavor that made every sip enjoyable. You can really taste the care that goes into it. Plus, inside 22 W., there’s a jewelry and bead shop, which was such a cool surprise—perfect for a little browsing while sipping on a delicious drink. Highly recommend checking it out!
reviews_data.owner_answer: I'm so glad you loved the chai window and shop! Thank you so much for such a kind review and we look forward to welcoming you back soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I love visiting the Chai Window!! The little details and love that go into each drink makes it so special. Everything from the little flowers on each cup, having oat milk as the standard, and the fabulous store branding/decorations. I have my frequent customer punch card always on hand just in case I need a little pick-me-up when I'm running errands in Plaza Midwood. I truly cannot recommend it enough!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Awe this makes me so happy! I'm so glad you loved all the little details and your time here at the shop and chai window. We'll see you again soon on your next errand run!

reviews_data.review_text: Mary - wonderful chai & concept & love to support small businesses thriving energy!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for coming to visit us Prin! It was a joy to make chai for you all and I look forward to seeing you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: My friend and I recently visited The Chai Window, and it was such a lovely experience! From the moment we walked in, the warm and cozy shop made us feel right at home. The aesthetic is perfect—soft lighting, beautiful decor, and a vibe that makes you want to stay all day. We ordered our chai, and it was absolutely delicious! The blend of spices was perfect, and it had just the right amount of sweetness—definitely the best chai we've had in a while.
reviews_data.owner_answer: This is the best! I'm so glad you and your friend felt so welcomed and we hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: The best chai I’ve ever had! Feels so cozy and homey; my new favorite spot!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your kind review and I'm so glad you enjoyed your time at The Chai Window! We will see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Absolutely obsessed! Such a little gem in CLT! I really appreciate as a vegan that it is organic chai with oat milk & coconut sugar. The cutest little spot, indoor and outdoor seating perfect for a coffee date with a friend or getting work done on a spring day, and the most kind staff! Will definitely be a frequent customer 😊
reviews_data.owner_answer: Awe yay! We put so much care into each cup of chai and are so glad you loved it and the full experience! We cannot wait to welcome you back soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
Beautiful aesthetic, and a really cute spot, but the only unfortunate part is that this is not authentic chai (we had the one item on the menu called ‘hot chai’). I was really excited for true authentic Indian chai but unfortunately this is the same sweet concoction a Starbucks would serve up in the name of chai. It’s the wrong flavor profile, the wrong color, and the wrong temperature.
I think this place has a lot of potential - they just need to research the product. Or perhaps it’s catering to the more American audience, but this is definitely what an Indian would call chai. Sorry I really wanted to like the place. I’m going to visit again in a few months to see if the product gets a taste-lift.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We know everyone’s taste in chai is a little different so thanks so much for coming to try our house made chai! I appreciate your feedback and you’re always welcome here.

reviews_data.review_text:
Came here on a whim with a group of friends, as we were just passing through. We did see the promotion on Instagram ahead of time, so we decided to give it a try. Was really looking forward to it, as i love a good iced chai. Unfortunately, this chai was extremely disappointing.

It tasted like the very top of an iced chai: watered down, a weak flavor profile, no richness, and overall just incredibly underwhelming. I’m no chai connoisseur despite my love of the stuff, but I wouldn’t be able to recommend this place off the flavor of the chai. This is pretty important considering it’s the main appeal of the place. I was also really looking forward to trying the chai ice cream sandwiches in the future, but now I’m reluctant because of my experience.

Seems to be a fairly new establishment, so i hope they improve on things in the future!

A couple side notes: The customer service was great, and the design of the building is very nice. The cups are cute and social media worthy. The location is along the side of a busy road, so it’s very easy to miss.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you so much for sharing your feedback with us. We hear what you're saying and it sounds like your cup was not up to our standards as the quality of rich, spiced chai that we pride ourselves on. We’d love the chance to make it right—please stop by during business hours, and my team and I would like to treat you to a cup of chai on us!

We also appreciate your kind words about our service and the design of our space. We’re always working to improve, and your feedback means a lot to us as a new business. We hope to welcome you back soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
I wish I could give The Chai Window 5+ stars 🫶✨ When I found this hidden gem, I was over the moon with my experience — the iced chai was delicious, the owner was so hospitable & kind, and the small business inside the house is so cutie!

Definitely worth a try — 10/10
reviews_data.owner_answer: Wow, thank you for such a sweet review! We’re beyond thrilled that you enjoyed our chai and felt at home in our space. We can’t wait to welcome you back for another Sip + Shop soon!

reviews_data.review_text: My friend and I absolutely adored this place! The woman running it was so sweet. The chai itself is amazing. It has a natural taste no extra sweeteners allowing you to taste all the spices in the tea. The place also has a little shop connected to it called Twenty Two West. Everything is handmade. We enjoyed sipping and shopping (:
reviews_data.owner_answer: I’m so glad you and your friend loved the shop and chai! We put a lot of care into our house made chai - muddling the spices, steeping the organic Assam tea, sourcing our oat milk and using organic coconut sugar to get all those flavors in balance. And the same care goes into each piece of jewelry and art in the shop.  See you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: The tastiest chai in the neighborhood!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We love being in Plaza Midwood!

reviews_data.review_text: The best organic chai I have ever had! Will definitely make it apart of my morning routine
reviews_data.owner_answer: I’m so glad you love the chai! We’ll see you soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Ultra tasty chai from ultra friendly people 🫖
reviews_data.owner_answer: I’m so glad you love the chai!

Definitely worth a try — 10/10
reviews_data.owner_answer: Wow, thank you for such a sweet review! We’re beyond thrilled that you enjoyed our chai and felt at home in our space. We can’t wait to welcome you back for another Sip + Shop soon!

reviews_data.review_text: My friend and I absolutely adored this place! The woman running it was so sweet. The chai itself is amazing. It has a natural taste no extra sweeteners allowing you to taste all the spices in the tea. The place also has a little shop connected to it called Twenty Two West. Everything is handmade. We enjoyed sipping and shopping (:
reviews_data.owner_answer: I’m so glad you and your friend loved the shop and chai! We put a lot of care into our house made chai - muddling the spices, steeping the organic Assam tea, sourcing our oat milk and using organic coconut sugar to get all those flavors in balance. And the same care goes into each piece of jewelry and art in the shop.  See you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: The tastiest chai in the neighborhood!
reviews_data.owner_answer: We love being in Plaza Midwood!

reviews_data.review_text: The best organic chai I have ever had! Will definitely make it apart of my morning routine
reviews_data.owner_answer: I’m so glad you love the chai! We’ll see you soon!

raw_data.description: Embedded in the Twenty Two West studio and storefront is our cozy Chai Window, where we serve up cups of beautifully spiced, rich organic tea made in house from whole spices, velvety oat milk, and softly sweetened with coconut sugar. Each sip adds a layer of warmth, creating a true sip and shop experience!
